SPECIFIC TERMS FOR COSPAS-SARSAT BEACON GENERATOR:

1. EDUCATIONAL USE ONLY
   This beacon generator is designed exclusively for:
   - ADRASEC training and education
   - SATER emergency response exercises
   - Technical validation of SARSAT decoders (403 MHz)
   - Academic research in emergency beacon technology

2. FREQUENCY RESTRICTIONS
   - Generator operates at 403 MHz (training band)
   - SHALL NOT be modified to operate at 406 MHz COSPAS-SARSAT frequencies
   - SHALL NOT be used to generate real distress alerts

3. SAFETY DISCLAIMER
   - This device generates RF signals for training purposes only
   - Users must comply with local radio frequency regulations
   - Not intended for actual emergency use
   - False distress signal generation is prohibited

4. ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENTS
   When using or modifying this work, you must:
   - Credit the original development for ADRASEC training
   - Maintain references to COSPAS-SARSAT T.018 compliance
   - Include this license in any derivative works
   - Document any modifications made

5. DISTRIBUTION
   - May be shared freely within ADRASEC network
   - May be used by emergency services for training
   - Commercial sale or licensing is prohibited
   - Modifications must be shared under same license

To view a copy of this license, visit:
http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

